Teacher of Russian as the second language 
Private lessons of Russian for Dutch people
The courses were tailored to the level of each individual student to meet his/her private or business needs with the following main objectives: 

- inspiring the students not only to learn the Russian language, but also 
to learn more about the Russian country, its people, their culture and traditions;
- developing of communication skills;
- training in reading, listening, speaking and writing;
- explanation of grammar, vocabulary, elements of Russian culture and traditions 
in Dutch.       	 

In order to make the lessons more interesting, modern and classical music, films and books were used.

International Relations Department 
Responsible for international relations of the municipality of 
Vladivostok with the English speaking countries;
translation from English into Russian of the materials and documents sent to the Mayor and other departments of the City Hall; 
writing in English of letters, documents and other materials;
participation in negotiations, interpretation at the official meetings, ceremonies and during other activities; 
participation in business trips of municipal delegations abroad; 
sister city relations development with the cities of USA (Juneau, Tacoma, San Diego) and Republic of Korea (Pusan);
coordination of international projects.

Department of Tourism
Duties included inbound tourism development of the city, 
marketing and advertising of Vladivostok as a destination,
tourism infrastructure development,
cooperation with international tour operators and Vladivostok inbound tour companies to increase the number of incoming foreign tourists in the city.

Division of Religious and National Issues of the Department of Culture
Responsible for relations coordination of the municipal government with the national public organizations of Vladivostok: evaluation and analysis of the situation, 
response to requests, municipal support to preservation 
of national cultures and languages presented in the City of Vladivostok.
